          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/20/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Follow-up CHF, COPD, Afib.
HPI: 68yo male here for chronic disease management. Reports stable dyspnea on exertion -- can walk about 100 feet before needing rest. No orthopnea or PND. 2-pillow sleeper. Weights stable at home. Continues to smoke 1 ppd despite counseling.
PE: Lungs -- diminished bilaterally, scattered expiratory wheezes. CV -- irregularly irregular, no murmur. 1+ pitting edema bilateral ankles.
Assessment:
# CHF (I50.9): Stable NYHA Class III. BNP improved from 890 to 380. Continue furosemide, digoxin. Check BMP.
# Afib (I48.91): Rate controlled, HR 88. INR 2.4 therapeutic. Continue warfarin 5mg.
# COPD (J44.1): FEV1 42% predicted. Tiotropium + PRN albuterol. Smoking cessation counseled -- declined NRT again.
# BPH (N40.0): Nocturia x3. Discussed tamsulosin. Will start 0.4mg qhs.
# HTN (I10): BP 138/82. Acceptable given CHF meds.
Plan: Continue current regimen. Add tamsulosin 0.4mg qhs. INR in 2 weeks. Pulmonology referral for PFTs. Smoking cessation pamphlet given. Return 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>12/01/2025</td><td>Gretchen Lockard, MD</td><td>Acute Visit</td><td>CC: Worsening SOB, productive cough x 5 days, fever.
HPI: 68yo with COPD/CHF presents with acute worsening of dyspnea. Yellow-green sputum, fever to 101.4 at home. Unable to complete ADLs without stopping.
PE: T 100.8, HR 102, RR 24, O2 89% on RA. Lungs -- bilateral rhonchi, right base crackles. CV -- irregularly irregular, tachycardic. 2+ pedal edema.
CXR: Right lower lobe infiltrate, mild pulmonary congestion.
Assessment:
# COPD exacerbation with community-acquired pneumonia
# Acute on chronic systolic HF -- volume overloaded
Plan: Admit to observation. IV azithromycin + ceftriaxone. Increase furosemide to 80mg IV BID. Nebs q4h. O2 titrate to 90-92%. Hold warfarin, bridge with heparin drip. Telemetry monitoring.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>09/15/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT -- G0439
68yo male here for AWV.
Preventive:
- Lung cancer screening: LDCT ordered (30+ pack-years, active smoker).
- AAA screening: Not done -- discuss ultrasound.
- Colorectal cancer: Colonoscopy 2021, next 2031.
- Depression: PHQ-9 = 8 (mild).
- Fall risk: Timed Up and Go = 14 sec (borderline).
- Advance Directive: Updated, on file.
- Bone density: DEXA not indicated (male, no fracture risk).
Vaccines: Flu given. Shingrix dose 1 given.
Health Risk Assessment completed. Cognitive screen normal (Mini-Cog 4/5).</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
